==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ascocarp
<hw>As"co*carp</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'asko`s</grk> a bladder + <grk>karpo`s</grk> fruit.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>In ascomycetous fungi, the spherical, discoid, or
cup-shaped body within which the asci are collected, and which
constitutes the mature fructification. The different forms are known in
mycology under distinct names. Called also <altname>spore
fruit</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>ascocarpous</ent>⟦br⟧
